{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, this may lead to an overprotective reaction to a potential opportunity, such as New York City's schools' banning of ChatGPT from educational networks due to the risk of using it to cheat on assignments (Shen-Berro, 2023).",
    "Contrastingly, there may be a naïve acceptance of AI in education as 'the one' technology that will fundamentally change education provision and practice, overlooking and repeating high-profile failures of TEL in the past (Oppenheimer, 1997).",
    "It is, therefore, important to investigate the concerns of using chatbots in education to ensure safe and ethical use.",
    "This article briefly introduces the ethical implications of using platforms such as ChatGPT in education.",
    "The author focuses on data privacy, algorithmic bias, autonomy in learning, and the issue of plagiarism."
  ]
}